Caving and potholing is about going into caves to scramble, climb, traverse, and explore through water streams, meanders, narrow passages, massive chambers, and corners full of amazing formations underground. It requires no prior experience or equipment as there are caves for all levels, from simple walking to shafts requiring complex ropework, and you can borrow all gear from the club.
For more than 60 years, the caving club has been introducing the exciting underworld to many who had never visited a cave and who just wanted a new, completely different
experience. Many of them get addicted to the challenge and to the sense of adventure posed by caving.

CUCC organises caving trips every other weekend during Full Term time, so there are plenty of choices for you to try. Longer trips take place throughout the rest of the year. The club is not just about caving: while in Cambridge there are plenty of activities and socials that are regularly announced on the email list, including pub meets, training sessions, curry nights, talks, and many other outdoor activities.

Sign up to the email list to find out about upcoming training sessions or caving meets, and to suggest your initiatives and find other outdoor or underground mates. Check the calendar, come to the pub meet every Tuesday from 9pm, or join us on Facebook.
